CAPE TOWN - A thirty-year-old man, is set to app­ear in the Ngqamakhwe Ma­gistrate’s court in the Eastern Cape on Monday  for his alleged involvement in a kidnapping and ransom scheme. Hawks spokesperson Yolisa Mgolo­dela said the man will app­ear on charges of kidn­apping and armed rob­bery. He will be joi­ning his 30-year-old co-accused, Ephrem Gezew, who was arrested on January 27 and has been remanded in custody since. Mgolo­dela said that on Friday, January 20, at around 2pm, a 28-year-old Ethiop­ian national was dri­ving his vehicle on his way to his bus­iness when a white Polo vehi­cle allegedly blocked his way and kidnap­ped him. “The alleged kidnappers are said to have driven in Engcobo’s direct­ion where they are said to have demanded a ransom of R1 million to get the victim released,” Mgolo­dela said. The victim is report­ed to have been rele­ased on Sunday, Ja­nuary 23, when a ra­nsom of R250 000 was paid. “On Thursday, Janua­ry 27, at about 6pm a report was rece­ived from Msobomvu police station that Ethiopian nationals had brought in a kidna­pping suspect who has been remanded in custody si­nce his arrest and court appearance in Ngqamakhwe Magistrate­’s Court on Janua­ry 31. “The second suspect is reported to have been spotted in Butte­rworth Magistrate’s Court and was appreh­ended immediately. Hence, his first appe­arance for a formal bail application wit­h his alleged co-a­ccused was to be yesterday (Monday),” Mgolo­dela said. Cape Times